The paper deals with the maximum rate of space-time block codes (STBCs) for multiple transmit antennas, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The use of unitary weight matrices and the concept of full-diversity are also mentioned, which are common in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents coding gain expressions, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
